rComments: One of the English Departments best profs. Genuinely cares about what his students say in class, will go out of his way to be helpful. Don't miss a chance to take his classes!
Nice guy, good at leading discussions in seminar classes. Also, he can unintentionally be pretty funny sometimes.

Professor Uphaus really cares about his students, being a great listener in lecture and in office hours. Genuinely loves the material and generates a great environment for class discussion, wherein the students feel like we're coming up with the lecture material ourselves. Also awesome choice of texts!!
He's a good prof. You can tell he really he cares about his material, he's so passionate when talking about literary works.

When the professor asked what the students learned throughout the year they answered: Colonization is bad, gender politics are hard, slavery is bad, discrimination is wrong etc. Little was said about literature. When I took this course I was hoping to learn English, not History.
